{"version":3,"kind":"Article","sha256":"cc584b304443fc1d647b1de8beeffaf91692f9cf32a1c41062b981345f785096","slug":"pages.m15-wrap-up-type-i-and-type-ii-errors","location":"/pages/226-m15-wrap-up-type-i-and-type-ii-errors.md","dependencies":[],"frontmatter":{"title":"Wrap up Type I and Type II Errors","content_includes_title":false,"authors":[{"nameParsed":{"literal":"Shawn Wiggins","given":"Shawn","family":"Wiggins"},"name":"Shawn Wiggins","affiliations":["City College of San Francisco"],"id":"contributors-myst-generated-uid-0"}],"license":{"content":{"id":"CC-BY-4.0","url":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","name":"Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International","free":true,"CC":true}},"affiliations":[{"id":"City College of San Francisco","name":"City College of San Francisco"}],"numbering":{"title":{"offset":2}},"thumbnail":"/build/type_i_ii_errors-f0b885b94dc89187f4855bf561ec244c.png","exports":[{"format":"md","filename":"226-m15-wrap-up-type-i-and-type-ii-errors.md","url":"/build/226-m15-wrap-up-type-6ea3b020f9d13865373a90fd67c75720.md"}]},"mdast":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"block","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"It is important to remember to take into consideration the possibility of the occurrence of Type I or Type II error, when drawing conclusions from hypothesis tests. Thus:","position":{"start":{"line":3,"column":1},"end":{"line":3,"column":1}},"key":"bun4fYxsfO"}],"key":"ri8lEdatOL"},{"type":"list","ordered":false,"spread":false,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":8,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Whenever there is a failure to reject the null hypothesis, it is possible that a\nType II error has occurred. Thus, it is concluded from the results of the study,\nthat there are no significant differences, even though, in reality, there are\nsignificant differences.","position":{"start":{"line":5,"column":1},"end":{"line":5,"column":1}},"key":"hugXKqpxwL"}],"key":"YsWh9IN6Xr"}],"key":"wlihfuZpTc"},{"type":"listItem","spread":true,"position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":12,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Whenever the null hypothesis is rejected, it is possible that a Type I error has\nbeen committed. That is, it is concluded from the results of the study, that there\nare significant differences, when, in reality, there are no differences.","position":{"start":{"line":9,"column":1},"end":{"line":9,"column":1}},"key":"Xd4u69bHN4"}],"key":"frDso9M3BM"}],"key":"uWYObthJFF"}],"key":"cWobweD4Xq"},{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"However, it is not possible to know when either Type I or Type II error has occurred.","position":{"start":{"line":13,"column":1},"end":{"line":13,"column":1}},"key":"mjHipfSPBa"}],"key":"MT4SU0BmMG"},{"type":"container","kind":"figure","children":[{"type":"image","url":"/build/type_i_ii_errors-f0b885b94dc89187f4855bf561ec244c.png","alt":"A table describing when errors occur. When H_0 is true, and we reject H_0, we have made a Type I error. If we fail to reject H_0, this is the correct decision. When H_0 is false (H_a is true), and we reject H_0, we have made the correct decision. If we fail to reject H_0, this is a type II error.","key":"OLb5eud5hA","urlSource":"images/type_i_ii_errors.png"},{"type":"caption","children":[{"type":"paragraph","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"A table describing when errors occur. When H_0 is true, and we reject H_0, we have made a Type I error. If we fail to reject H_0, this is the correct decision. When H_0 is false (H_a is true), and we reject H_0, we have made the correct decision. If we fail to reject H_0, this is a type II error.","position":{"start":{"line":18,"column":1},"end":{"line":18,"column":1}},"key":"TnXm505a6T"}],"key":"KyhbVgCf5M"}],"key":"Q7DN4kdgHa"}],"enumerator":"1","key":"IphOwAxdef"},{"type":"heading","depth":2,"position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"End-of-Lesson","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":1},"end":{"line":21,"column":1}},"key":"zQIOgiD3BZ"}],"identifier":"end-of-lesson","label":"End-of-Lesson","html_id":"end-of-lesson","implicit":true,"key":"TvJsDxhztJ"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"\t\tQuestions","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":1},"end":{"line":22,"column":1}},"key":"veb42JljY5"},{"type":"admonition","kind":"note","children":[{"type":"admonitionTitle","children":[{"type":"text","value":"Note","key":"yRbXd9N0Jm"}],"key":"pzR8LocBhE"},{"type":"code","lang":"","value":"**My Response**\n\nAbout Type I and II Errors\n\n*(Interactive activity — available in the OLI platform)*","position":{"start":{"line":25,"column":1},"end":{"line":29,"column":1}},"key":"JPCeoj40pV"}],"key":"RKchxKh7yJ"}],"key":"hnQFITcHW7"}],"key":"bjr6KSjbf5"},"references":{"cite":{"order":[],"data":{}}},"footer":{"navigation":{"prev":{"title":"Type I and Type II Errors","url":"/pages/m15-type-i-and-type-ii-errors","group":"Unit 5: Inference"},"next":{"title":"Introduction","short_title":"Module 16: Inference for Relationships","url":"/pages/m16-introduction","group":"Unit 5: Inference"}}},"domain":"http://localhost:3001"}